CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HRMS workflow currently uses keyword-based intent classification and
the deprecated collection_agents state field. This task rewrites it
to match the pattern established in RMS workflow (Task 4.2 + 4.2.1):

  - LLM intent classifier via PydanticOutputParser, returning
    domain / collection / persona / confidence / reasoning.
  - Defense-in-depth: HIGH proceeds silently, MEDIUM/LOW appends
    a soft correction; OUT_OF_DOMAIN routes to permission_blocked.
  - DB-driven Gate 2 via AuthController.check_agent_access().
  - State uses add_messages channel for the messages field.
  - Nodes return only NEW messages (not appended to old).

HRMS collections (from dpah_collections seed):
  - hrms_leave_data: leave types, leave requests, leave approvals.
  - hrms_salarydata: payslips (creator), view own payslip (reviewer),
    view any payslip (approver).

HRMS personas: CREATOR / REVIEWER / APPROVER (same as RMS).

Agent name convention: HRMS_{COLLECTION_SUFFIX}_{PERSONA}
  e.g., HRMS_LEAVE_DATA_CREATOR, HRMS_SALARYDATA_REVIEWER.

